				Table 2 - Trial: Law 1
			-
				-
					Table 2 - Trial: Law 1: Item a
				-
					-
						The penal sum in an action by solemn deposit shall be either 500 asses or
						50 asses ... It shall be argued by solemn deposit with 500 asses, when the
						property is valued at 1,000 asses or more, but with 50 asses, when the
						property is valued at less than 1,000 asses. But if the controversy is
						about the freedom of a person, although the person may be very valuable,
						yet the case shall be argued by a solemn deposit of 50 asses. ...
					-
