				-
					If one has obtained an unjustifiable grant of interim possession and if his
					adversary wishes ... the magistrate shall grant three arbiters; by their
					arbitration ... the unjustifiable holder of interim possession shall settle the
					plaintiff's loss of enjoyment of the thing by paying double damages.
